+- **Practice mode deployment (Epic 8 / FR26):** **`PHARMA_RD_DEPLOYMENT_PROFILE`** — **`practice`** (default), **`staging`**, or **`production`**. **Practice** is the demo-oriented build: **public/mock sources** are allowed and **enterprise SSO is not required** for MVP (**FR34** is roadmap). Structured JSON logs include **`deployment_profile`** on pipeline start (`run_started` / `pipeline_resume`). Insight **`report.md`** / **`report.html`** add a **Run summary** line for **`practice`** only. **`PHARMA_RD_PRACTICE_CONSUMER_MOCK`** still controls the consumer fixture default when **`PHARMA_RD_CONSUMER_FEEDBACK_PATH`** is unset.
+- **Coarse access control (Epic 8 / FR32, NFR-S2):** Optional **`PHARMA_RD_ARTIFACT_ACCESS_TOKEN`** (max **8192** chars at load). When **set**, **`pharma-rd run`**, **`runs`**, **`status`**, and **`retry-stage`** require **`PHARMA_RD_CLI_ACCESS_TOKEN`** in the process environment to **match** (constant-time compare). **Unset** = no CLI guard (default for local dev). **Not** enforced for the in-process **`scheduler`** job (scheduled runs use **`enforce_cli_access=False`**). **Shared storage:** restrict **Unix permissions** on **`PHARMA_RD_DB_PATH`**, **`PHARMA_RD_ARTIFACTS_ROOT`**, and log destinations; **never** commit real tokens to git (NFR-S1). **`pharma-rd scheduler`** and **`--version` / help** do **not** require the CLI token.
 - **Internal research (Epic 3 / FR7):** **`PHARMA_RD_INTERNAL_RESEARCH_PATH`** — optional path to a **single `.json` file** or a **directory** of **`*.json`** files. Each JSON file is either **one object** or an **array of objects** with required **`title`** and **`summary`** strings; optional **`reference`** and **`source_label`**. Relative paths resolve from the process **current working directory**. When **unset**, the clinical artifact includes an explicit **“not configured”** note (NFR-I1). **`PHARMA_RD_INTERNAL_RESEARCH_MAX_FILE_BYTES`** (default **262144**) caps per-file read size. Sample fixture: **`tests/fixtures/internal_research/sample.json`** (use its path in `.env` for practice demos).
