+- **GPT synthesis (Epic 6 / story 6.5):** **`PHARMA_RD_SYNTHESIS_MODE`** — **`gpt`** (default) or **`deterministic`**. With **`gpt`** and **`PHARMA_RD_OPENAI_API_KEY`** set, the synthesis stage calls **OpenAI** (same **`PHARMA_RD_OPENAI_MODEL`** as other GPT steps, default **`gpt-4o`**) using JSON mode; the user prompt includes serialized **`ClinicalOutput`**, **`CompetitorOutput`**, and **`ConsumerOutput`** (including optional **`clinical_gpt_analysis`**, **`competitor_gpt_analysis`**, **`consumer_gpt_analysis`** when present). **`ranking_criteria_version`** is **`gpt_strategy_v1`**. **`aggregated_upstream_gaps`** (including **`[synthesis]`** truncation notes) and **`scan_summary_lines`** are still assembled **deterministically** from upstream artifacts for transparency. **`PHARMA_RD_OPENAI_SYNTHESIS_TIMEOUT_SECONDS`** (default **180**) bounds the synthesis request (NFR-P1). **Failure policy:** invalid JSON or **`SynthesisOutput`** validation failure triggers **one** bounded retry with a repair prompt; then the stage **fails** with an operator-oriented error (**no** silent fallback to deterministic). With **`gpt`** and **no** API key, synthesis **fails** unless you set **`PHARMA_RD_SYNTHESIS_MODE=deterministic`**. **`deterministic`** uses the legacy cross-domain ranking path (**`cross_domain_v1`**) without LLM—use for **CI/offline** without a key. **`pytest`** defaults **`PHARMA_RD_SYNTHESIS_MODE=deterministic`** in **`tests/conftest.py`**. Large upstream lists are capped per domain (**40** items per list) before prompting; see **`pharma_rd/integrations/openai_synthesis.py`**.
+- **Delivery / insight report (Epic 7 / FR18–FR19, FR22):** The delivery stage reads **`SynthesisOutput`** in memory from the runner, writes a **Markdown** report to **`{artifacts_root}/{run_id}/delivery/report.md`** and a **static HTML** twin to **`{artifacts_root}/{run_id}/delivery/report.html`** (UTF-8, atomic writes). **After** **`report.html`** exists on disk, the stage optionally **POST**s a **Slack Block Kit** notification when **`PHARMA_RD_SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL`** is set (see **Slack notifications** below); then it runs **distribution** (next bullet). It persists **`DeliveryOutput`** **`schema_version` 3** as **`{artifacts_root}/{run_id}/delivery/output.json`** with **`report_relative_path`**, **`report_format`** (**`markdown`**), **`report_byte_size`**, **`report_html_relative_path`**, **`report_html_byte_size`**, **`distribution_channel`** / **`distribution_status`** / **`distribution_detail`** (FR19), plus **`slack_notify_status`** / **`slack_notify_detail`** when Slack is used or skipped. **FR22 (human judgment):** disclaimer language is embedded in the **run summary** (executive callout), **each ranked opportunity**, the **Governance and disclaimer** section, and an HTML **`<footer>`**; wording lives in **`pharma_rd/agents/delivery.py`** for a single edit point. The report body also includes FR27/FR28 fields in the summary and ranked opportunities (no re-ranking).
+- **GPT report narrative (Epic 7 / story 7.6):** **`PHARMA_RD_REPORT_RENDERER`** — **`template`** (default, CI) or **`gpt`**. With **`gpt`** and **`PHARMA_RD_OPENAI_API_KEY`**, delivery calls OpenAI once (JSON response with **`report_html`** body fragment + **`report_markdown`** + optional **`slack_executive_excerpt`**). HTML is sanitized with **`nh3`** before write (allowlist tags; **no** `<script>`). A trusted shell adds **`<!DOCTYPE>`**, charset, base CSS, and the FR26 practice banner when applicable. If the model omits required FR22 phrases, the stage **prepends** the executive FR22 banner. **`PHARMA_RD_OPENAI_REPORT_DELIVERY_TIMEOUT_SECONDS`** (default **150**) bounds the call (NFR-P1). **`PHARMA_RD_REPORT_GPT_FALLBACK_ON_ERROR`** (default **true**): on API/parse failure, delivery **falls back** to the string-template renderer and logs **`delivery_gpt_fallback`** (NFR-R1). **`gpt`** without an API key logs **`delivery_gpt_skipped_no_key`** and uses the template. Slack uses **`slack_executive_excerpt`** for the executive block when present (truncated). Implementation: **`pharma_rd/integrations/openai_report_delivery.py`**, **`report_html_sanitize.py`**.
+- **Slack notifications (Epic 7 / FR19 extension):** **`PHARMA_RD_SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL`** — optional **incoming webhook** URL ([Slack incoming webhooks](https://api.slack.com/messaging/webhooks)). When **unset** or empty, **no** HTTP request is made; structured logs record **`slack_notify_skipped`** (INFO). When set, the pipeline sends **`blocks`** (Block Kit) plus a plain **`text`** fallback. The message includes **UTC run date** (calendar date at delivery execution), **pharma_RD** branding, **`signal_characterization`**, top ranked opportunities, therapeutic-area and competitor-watchlist scope from settings, an **FR22** disclaimer aligned with the report, and the **on-disk absolute path** to **`report.html`** (MVP). **`PHARMA_RD_SLACK_WEBHOOK_TIMEOUT_SECONDS`** defaults to **10** seconds (separate from connector HTTP). Webhook failures do **not** fail the delivery stage; logs use **`slack_notify_failed`** with actionable detail (**no** full URL or secrets). Implementation: **`pharma_rd/integrations/slack_insight_notification.py`**.
+- **Report distribution (Epic 7 / FR19):** **`PHARMA_RD_DISTRIBUTION_CHANNEL`** — **`none`** (default, explicit skip in logs), **`file_drop`**, or **`smtp`**. **File drop (MVP):** set **`PHARMA_RD_DISTRIBUTION_DROP_DIR`** to a directory root; after **`report.md`** and **`report.html`** are written, the pipeline copies them to **`{drop_dir}/rd/{run_id}/`** and **`{drop_dir}/marketing/{run_id}/`** and writes **`{drop_dir}/{run_id}/manifest.json`** with absolute paths for audit (including HTML paths when present). **`smtp`** is reserved: distribution logs **`distribution_failed`** with **`error_type=smtp_not_implemented`** and **`distribution_status=failed`** (no credentials logged). Placeholder recipient envs for future SMTP: **`PHARMA_RD_RD_RECIPIENT_EMAIL`**, **`PHARMA_RD_MARKETING_RECIPIENT_EMAIL`**. **Product choice (fail-fast):** distribution failures do **not** abort the delivery stage—the run still writes **`DeliveryOutput`** with **`distribution_status=failed`** and structured **`distribution_failed`** logs (NFR-R1).
+- **For recipients (Epic 7 / FR20–FR21, NFR-P2, FR22):** **R&D** and **marketing** receive the **same** files for each **`run_id`** (separate folders for role audit only). **Markdown:** open **`report.md`** in any text editor or Markdown-aware tool (e.g. **VS Code**, **Cursor**, GitHub/GitLab preview). **Browser (no extension):** double-click **`report.html`** or open it via **File → Open** in **Chrome**, **Edge**, or **Safari** (`file://` is fine for local copies). **Email:** attaching **`report.md`** yields readable plain text; **`report.html`** can be opened in a browser if the mail client saves attachments. No **pharma_RD**-specific desktop client is required. **FR22:** read the executive callout, per-opportunity lines, governance section, and HTML footer so **recommendations** are clearly **not approvals** and **pursuit remains human-owned**.
 
